<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>4</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> Why did <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>I</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (not TK) designed this board? (<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:fuchsia;font-family:helvetica;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>1</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->) Because I can. (<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:fuchsia;font-family:helvetica;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>2</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->) I like making BBSs and Websites - and its a rare gift to be able to make one that alot of people will use and enjoy. (<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:fuchsia;font-family:helvetica;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>3</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->) I thought it might get under Lisa's skin.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>5</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Eecck! How could you admit that last one?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Hey. I'm no saint. Let he who is without sin cast the first flame, yadda, yadda, yadda.  I NEVER expected Slipstream to close or for SS: UG to be going it alone. I thought SlipstreamBBS would reopen and SS: UG would function as a sideboard much like EFCL does for Trekbbs. It was my original idea that SS: UG would funtion as an independent SlipstreamBBS lounge - hence the name &quot;Slipstream Underground&quot;. When SlipstreamBBS didn't reopen we had to scale the project up to turn it into a completely independent board.<br>
 <br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>6.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Do you think Slipstream Unerground had anything to do with SlipstreamBBS closing?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Yes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:fuchsia;font-family:helvetica;">However</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> I think Lisa is being 100% truthful when she says the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>main reason</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> SlipstreamBBS closed was due to lack of money (although I think Trekbbs makes more than enough to carry SSBBS's weight, but as an independent business model it failed). But the money situation wasn't new by any means, this was the black cloud hanging over SSBBS for a long time. There are three main events that caused the BBS to close that day instead of two months ago or two years from now. (<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;font-family:helvetica;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Also notice that SSBBS didn't close until a few days after Lisa reached partner status money wise</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->.)<br>
<br>
(<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>1</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->) <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;font-family:helvetica;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The downward turn of fan opinion about the show meant that there was little hope of the numbers building up to improve the money situation</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->, however this too was a problem realized months ago. Thats why they didn't care if registeration was turned off, by that point they had already given up on Slipstream's numbers building up to hold its own weight. By turning registeration off they saved on bandwidth (although this would only amount to a dime in a bucket), and would serve to slowly filter down the community whos closing now seemed like an unescapable fact. In was only a matter of when.<br>
<br>
(<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>2</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->) <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;font-family:helvetica;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Enter Trollkingdom</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->. Lisa had been dealing with TKers for something like two years now. She was no stranger to them and could very well be considered as much an expert on TK as TK was on her. She knew what methods worked against them and what methods didn't. She was no novice in this area. So then why the panic flat out permabanning of the entire TK population in less than two hours? SlipstreamBBS was already a sinking ship, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">SSBBS was only keeping its head above water so long as it could run by itself and Lisa &amp; Chris didn't have to spend time on a BBS that wasn't turning a profit.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> An influx of new TK members didn't mean an attack of spam threads or flames - Lisa could handle those in her sleep. An influx of new TK members meant a harder to run BBS due to completely legit threads. TK members are nothing if not vocal. The fact that TK had no intention of trolling SSBBS and the fact that they were being welcomed with open arms was almost too much for Lisa to bare. No way was she going to going to spend extra time on a dying BBS so that a group of people shes come to hate could make friends with her other board. <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Lisa's never been afraid of TK spam attacks or flames, her biggest fear is that TK will actually make friends with the community.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Ask yourself why TK links are edited out at Trekbbs yet spam threads are simply locked. For this reason all TK members were banned.<br>
<br>
(<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>3</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->) <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;font-family:helvetica;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Enter SlipstreamBBS Exposed.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> By the time the OQ threads were leaked a number of SSBBS members were already becoming friends with TK members and even posting on the TK board. It had appeared that banning them had not helped and the ball was already in motion. (Later Lisa would try to make a few last ditch efforts to cut this string by actually banning Slipstream members themselves who had contact with the TKers). The friendship continued to grow. Many didn't understand why all these people were being banned and began to question how SlipstreamBBS was being ran. When the OQ threads were released it tiped the scales in a big way. Much more than even when Trekbbs Exposed was released. Trekbbser's had years to realize what was going on in the BR before it came out in public, the Slipstreamers on the other hand were not prepared for what they found. Its was like someone literally pushed them into a freezing lake. Almost every person on the board became interested in how SlipstreamBBS was being run. Great debates followed. <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;font-family:helvetica;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>HOWEVER this is NOT when Slipstream closed. Slipstream's doors shut AFTER the OQ debates had been resolved and the general membership began looking at &quot;Ok, where do we go from here?&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> Its the answers that started coming out to that question which scared Lisa. The general membersip was no longer angry but they didn't want a return to status quo either. <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">This meant Lisa would have to do more work on a BBS that was most likely going to be ditched anyway.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Also changing how Slipstream was run would undoubtly effect Trekbbs as well since the posters there would claim double standard. Lisa shut down the BBS in hopes that people would become bored with the subject and wish to return to the status quo. However this did not happen, it was all to clear that the SSers WERE interested in how their BBS is run and they wanted to talk about it. Added to that was the fact that a bbs called 'Slipstream Underground' was formed where Lisa couldn't control the general climate of the conversation made a return to the status quo impossible. <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:lime;font-family:helvetica;">Even though the SSer's weren't angry and only wanted positive change, Lisa simply did not want to invest the time it would take to make that happen. So they shut it down.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
